{
  "local_port": 60818,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I want to activate my old whatsapp but I'm over seas and have the old number?",
  "response": "To activate your old WhatsApp account while overseas, you will need access to the phone number associated with that account. Here are the steps you can follow:\n\n1. **Ensure you have access to the old phone number:**\n   - If you can receive SMS or calls on that number, you're in a good position.\n   - If you have a SIM card for that old number, you can insert it into a compatible phone to receive the activation code.\n\n2. **Download WhatsApp:**\n   - If you haven't already, download and install WhatsApp on your phone.\n\n3. **Open WhatsApp:**\n   - Open the app and agree to the terms and conditions.\n\n4. **Enter your old phone number:**\n   - Choose your country code and enter your old phone number (the one associated with your WhatsApp account).\n\n5. **Receive the activation code:**\n   - WhatsApp will attempt to send an SMS to that number with a verification code. If the number is active and you have access, you should receive the code.\n   - If you don\u2019t receive the SMS, you can choose the option to receive a call instead for the verification code.\n\n6. **Enter the verification code:**\n   - Input the code you received via SMS or call into WhatsApp.\n\n7. **Restore your chat history (if applicable):**\n   - If you have a backup of your chat history (e.g., on Google Drive or iCloud), you will be prompted to restore it after activating your account.\n\n### If You Can't Receive SMS or Calls:\n- **Contact Your Carrier:** Reach out to your mobile service provider and check if they can enable roaming or help you access the number overseas.\n- **Use an Alternative Number:** If you can\u2019t access your old number, you might need to create a new WhatsApp account with a different number. However, this will mean you won't have access to your old messages unless you can recover that account.\n\n### Additional Considerations:\n- Be aware of any international roaming charges if you choose to use a SIM card associated with your old number while abroad.\n- Keep in mind that without access to the original number, recovering that WhatsApp account may be difficult.\n\nMake sure your internet connection is stable during the activation process for a smooth experience.",
